\details{
\subsection{Full mass balance of timber harvest}{

When 1 hectare of forest is harvested, the total biomass removed is:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Stem biomass} = \code{im_growing_stock} (tDM/ha)
\item \strong{Logging residues} (branches, tops) = 15\% of stem, tracked in \code{v73_prod_residues}
\item \strong{Total removed} = stem x 1.15
}

The model splits stem production between industrial roundwood (\code{vm_prod("wood")})
and woodfuel (\code{vm_prod("woodfuel")}). Only the industrial roundwood fraction enters
processing facilities and generates processing residues. Woodfuel is burned directly.
Logging residues already feed into MAgPIE's woodfuel supply (NOT reported here).

